Antwerp 26 gber 1682
my last tod you was on the 23tt cintt sence non from you, so this heebly
for novert of the inclosed accoumpt of sale of last month, which pleascts
enamin, & finding wright note accordingly, the present month will be no less, if
no more, & if there by you do not finde, that ony makeing of closh dosh
advance our English trade, then blame mee for doinge, non could is procure
payement accordingly, then all should be well, for which lly endeavour, butt
nent month I havee finde £809 sterlinx to paij for yd bills onely, so that
feare will much kinder my complayence in remises, batt D am sure
could you de lay one months drawing, that in gberI should remitt mo
less then what in sber I have to pay, & thento continece one month is
a short time, whover what you do is to comten: S finder a letter from m.
John bowdon & John gardner, by which they desire nre to pay a bill of
£500 aƒ 125 dd due z cinst & 6 dayes, which they havee accepted payable
at mij house, butt where as that trade is non of mine, so am vere yn
willing that to do yett thought good to advise you of to have yd opinion
whuh, I have the wing favoring before dul, I have no witt to them
mens peitation of yd answer remayn, I have complaints againe about
the N6 silver marn, & the good fathers desire to have the formar sorts

S I have some time de layd answer to yd of prico cintt: because
finde you will have still, that I am convitions, & yett you are not
pleaved to explaine yd self if & am so on yd preiudice, for that I would
say tolee minst, as partely you tough aboutt thestanding out debts not
beleaving what I wrot ps confes I did not wel to tell you that Joan
carlo de coninck hie widou is verspriet hus sisfer, beoeise the latter
was neidless, yett itt ie trae that 30 not mistake ther debts for
yd and as srae that the vidou the comuck owes mee above £8 00 flemish
more then what as for y acst. though I do not in the leest doabt
te finde satisfaction of ther yett the can do no more then all the
intrest, est beeng in generall a time of bad paey which pit mee often
to straights though f a of them converned aith mee have no less
shhen ƒ8800 aup loyed to tare my trade iutrim an assortemen
of tykes shall be schipped morming aboard peeter de wolf, otho will
saill the same day not inthitanding all endeavour s coon not afyett
pint of yd remay may cloathes hamble serous to al fiends

Jacording to my last have made up a small astortement
tykes there in fou laces for abual which I shall ship aff a
minday aboard & de wolf for london he sayles a mindey, here
is a kmys gaght commanded by rept fosebie I intend to send
half part of the laces by hom ander the dereifion of one of
hus schip called hactor lanc by which I have more often been
vere served whilst ment shall you the invoye & remaine
